      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "EAGLETURN (1) missed the kick when resuming last start over 1100m at Wyong but picked up late to finish fourth in an encouraging performance. Won't find this as tough and an extra 100m on a roomier track helps. Ready to win with the advantage of the inside alley. CURRUMBIN ALLEY (2) is back after a 33-week spell for a second campaign. Did a good job to be beaten just half a length on debut at Gunnedah last prep. Two recent trials should have him right up to the mark. Market watch on the first starter OLYMPIAN (4) from the Messara/Gavranich team. By The Autumn Sun from a Savabeel mare so he will need more ground in time but while fresh he cannot be ruled out. MORPETH (5) led but tired late in heavy ground at the end of 1280m at Muswellbrook recently. Has only raced twice so there is improvement to come. First starter BUTCH (3) has trialled a few times without impressing. Might need this run but keep an eye on the betting.",
